267
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,990
Anyway, let's open the window.

268
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:27,790
Unfinished 1 yen coins. And...

269
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:29,990
this is is a tube of oil paint.

270
00:15:32,190 --> 00:15:34,690
Look! Something's on the desk.

271
00:15:34,690 --> 00:15:36,590
Is it treasure?

272
00:15:40,890 --> 00:15:42,890
Hey, what's the matter?

273
00:15:45,690 --> 00:15:48,090
What is it? Speak up.

274
00:15:48,090 --> 00:15:50,690
Skeleton!

275
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:51,990
What?

276
00:15:57,690 --> 00:16:00,390
Who is that corpse?

277
00:16:00,390 --> 00:16:02,490
Didn't I tell you a while ago?

278
00:16:02,490 --> 00:16:06,290
There was an old person with skilled hands living here.

279
00:16:06,290 --> 00:16:07,990
He's probably the one who carved the 1 yen coin

280
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:10,790
and wrote those secret codes.

281
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:13,390
He wasn't killed, was he?

282
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:18,390
No. He passed away while writing a letter to your aunt.

283
00:16:19,990 --> 00:16:22,190
Looks like he had a bad heart.

284
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:25,990
But how did he know about this hidden room?

285
00:16:25,990 --> 00:16:27,090
The only ones who knew about it

286
00:16:27,090 --> 00:16:30,890
were my uncle and aunt who lived here.

287
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:32,590
There's one other, isn't there?

288
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:34,290
Before your uncle died,

289
00:16:34,290 --> 00:16:37,690
there was a person who was and out of this house.

290
00:16:37,690 --> 00:16:39,890
Before my uncle died?

291
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:41,790
Oh, that painting!

292
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:46,590
Right. The portrait of your aunt and uncle

293
00:16:46,590 --> 00:16:48,690
is that artist who painted that picture.

294
00:16:48,690 --> 00:16:51,690
He probably heard about this hidden room from your uncle

295
00:16:51,690 --> 00:16:53,690
while doing the painting.

296
00:16:53,690 --> 00:16:57,390
But why did he have to live and hide here?

297
00:16:57,390 --> 00:17:01,290
And why he send those coded letters to my aunt?

298
00:17:01,290 --> 00:17:03,990
That reason is probably this.

299
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:06,490
Huh? What's this?

300
00:17:06,490 --> 00:17:08,090
This is...

301
00:17:08,090 --> 00:17:10,490
A 20 dollar bill printing plate?

302
00:17:10,490 --> 00:17:12,290
Counterfeit!

303
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:16,690
Right. He was probably asked by someone to make it.

304
00:17:16,690 --> 00:17:19,990
But it bothered him and he disappeared with the plate.

305
00:17:19,990 --> 00:17:23,690
To escape from that somebody, he hid and lived here.

306
00:17:24,490 --> 00:17:26,590
Those letters he wrote to your aunt

307
00:17:26,590 --> 00:17:29,790
were to show her his appreciation for letting him live here.

308
00:17:29,790 --> 00:17:32,690
He used the secret code because he didn't want anybody,

309
00:17:32,690 --> 00:17:36,090
other than your aunt, to know where he was.

310
00:17:36,090 --> 00:17:41,290
Then, that person who was peeking into my aunt's mailbox was...

311
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:44,490
Yes, it's the person who order the counterfeit.

312
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:47,390
And the person who slashed up the toys you hid

313
00:17:47,390 --> 00:17:48,590
is also the same person.

314
00:17:48,590 --> 00:17:50,590
An excellent answer.

315
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:56,240
I thought I'd found where that guy was

316
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:59,440
and where he hid the printing plate.

317
00:17:59,440 --> 00:18:01,640
But there were only toys in the box

318
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:05,540
and I slashed them up.

319
00:18:05,540 --> 00:18:08,740
I heard that he was friendly with the owner of this house

320
00:18:08,740 --> 00:18:11,240
and suspected this was the place,

321
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:14,840
but I didn't know there was a hidden room.

322
00:18:14,840 --> 00:18:17,240
Thanks, kids.

323
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:18,840
You rat!

324
00:18:21,540 --> 00:18:26,040
Don't move! I don't want to make a murderer of myself.

325
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:29,740
And if you make the wrong move and the bullet hits the plate,

326
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:32,740
it won't be of any use.

327
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,140
Gosh!

328
00:18:39,940 --> 00:18:43,040
Young lady.

329
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:45,040
That's right, you.

330
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,740
Get that printing plate from the old man

331
00:18:47,740 --> 00:18:50,340
and bring it over here.

332
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:58,240
That's it. You're a good girl.

333
00:18:58,240 --> 00:19:00,040
If you can bring it right over to me,

334
00:19:00,040 --> 00:19:03,040
I'll give you a reward.

335
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:11,440
You brat! You want to get blown away?

336
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:15,940
Don't panic. I'll give it to you later.

337
00:19:16,740 --> 00:19:20,640
Tomoaki Okuda.

338
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:22,740
Why do you know my name?

339
00:19:22,740 --> 00:19:25,240
I heard it from that person a while ago.

340
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:29,340
How can a corpse talk?

341
00:19:29,340 --> 00:19:32,040
Listen. If you listen closely, you can hear him.

342
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:35,340
His spirit is probably still wandering around here.

343
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:39,740
You brat! If you make anymore wise-cracks...

344
00:19:39,740 --> 00:19:42,340
Tomoaki Okuda.

345
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:47,940
Tomoaki Okuda.

346
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:52,440
Tomoaki Okuda.

347
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:57,140
Tomoaki Okuda.

348
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:05,240
Well, just as promised, I'll give you this.

349
00:20:08,540 --> 00:20:10,240
Take it!

350
00:20:17,840 --> 00:20:20,340
Conan! Let's escape while we can!

351
00:20:20,340 --> 00:20:21,540
Huh?

352
00:20:21,540 --> 00:20:24,540
That's right! If that ghost appears again...

353
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:26,840
Oh, that voice...

354
00:20:26,840 --> 00:20:28,740
It's this.

355
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:31,440
The Yaiba Reco-changer!

356
00:20:31,440 --> 00:20:33,640
I recorded my voice

357
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,740
and played it over and over again in slow.

358
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:41,540
But how did you know that guy's name?

359
00:20:41,540 --> 00:20:46,040
It was written in secret code on that unfinished letter on the desk.

360
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,840
It said, "I don't want this masterpiece

361
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:50,940
to get in the hands of Tomoaki Okuda".

362
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:52,640
I see.

363
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:55,440
He wanted to leave this masterpiece in the hands of my aunt

364
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:56,940
whom he was indebted to in the past

365
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:59,040
so he left the secret codes in this house

366
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:02,340
to let her know where he was.

367
00:21:02,340 --> 00:21:06,040
Hey. That aunt... what is she doing now?

368
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:09,740
She passed away last year, at age 76.

369
00:21:09,740 --> 00:21:12,340
She never got married.

370
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:21,240
Maybe it wasn't only because he was indebted to her in the past.

371
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:50,640
Two hours later, the police arrived

372
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:52,840
and Tomoaki Okuda was arrested.

373
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:55,540
We finally got to go home.

374
00:22:58,140 --> 00:23:00,340
But I don't understand.

375
00:23:00,340 --> 00:23:01,540
Huh?

376
00:23:01,540 --> 00:23:05,440
You know, those words that your father said...

377
00:23:05,440 --> 00:23:08,240
Dr. Agasa, you're like the sun!

378
00:23:08,940 --> 00:23:14,440
For a while after that, he called me "Dr. Sun".

379
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:16,940
Oh, that.

380
00:23:16,940 --> 00:23:18,740
It's just a joke.

381
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:20,240
A joke?

382
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:23,440
Look at our name with this decoding chart.

383
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:24,440
Huh?

384
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,840
They're all suns, aren't they?

385
00:23:29,840 --> 00:23:32,040
I see!

386
00:23:33,940 --> 00:23:36,040
This is funny!

387
00:23:40,540 --> 00:23:43,140
I'm Dr. Sun!

388
00:23:46,840 --> 00:23:48,440
"Next Episode" -What?

389
00:23:49,540 --> 00:23:51,640
There's somebody outside!

390
00:23:57,040 --> 00:23:59,440
It's finally just us.

391
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:02,140
Even we were being fooled,

392
00:24:02,140 --> 00:24:03,840
it's absolutely unforgivable!

393
00:24:07,440 --> 00:24:09,240
Conan!

394
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,740
Run, Mitsuhiko!

395
00:24:11,940 --> 00:24:13,440
Next Conan,

396
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:16,760
"Disappearance of the Youth Detective Squad"

397
00:24:17,340 --> 00:24:19,640
Next Conan's Hint:

398
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:22,140
"Number of dolls"

399
00:24:22,140 --> 00:24:24,140
The Youth Detective Squad does a great job on the next episode too.

400
00:24:24,140 --> 00:24:25,940
Looks like Mitsuhiko will be the main character.

